# <%= appName %> — Modular Monolith

Single deployable application with **strict module boundaries**. Each feature is a self-contained module under `src/modules/<feature>/`.

## Structure

```
src/
  modules/<feature>/   # controller, service, repository, routes, tests
  shared/
    kernel/            # shared domain primitives
    contracts/         # cross-module interfaces
    infrastructure/    # DB, cache, messaging adapters
  bootstrap/             # module registration
```

## Rules

1. Modules do not import sibling modules directly — use `shared/contracts` or events.
2. `shared/kernel` has no dependency on `src/modules`.
3. Use `my make module <name>` to scaffold new feature modules.

See `.architecture/MODULE_BOUNDARIES.md`.
